005package edu.wpi.first.networktables;
006
007import java.util.Objects;
008
009/** A network table entry value. */
010@SuppressWarnings("PMD.MethodReturnsInternalArray")
011public final class NetworkTableValue {
012  NetworkTableValue(NetworkTableType type, Object value, long time) {
013    m_type = type;
014    m_value = value;
015    m_time = time;
016  }
017
018  NetworkTableValue(NetworkTableType type, Object value) {
019    this(type, value, NetworkTablesJNI.now());
020  }
021
022  NetworkTableValue(int type, Object value, long time) {
023    this(NetworkTableType.getFromInt(type), value, time);
024  }
025
026  /**
027   * Get the data type.
028   *
029   * @return The type.
030   */
031  public NetworkTableType getType() {
032    return m_type;
033  }
034
035  /**
036   * Get the data value stored.
037   *
038   * @return The type.
039   */
040  public Object getValue() {
041    return m_value;
042  }
043
044  /**
045   * Get the creation time of the value.
046   *
047   * @return The time, in the units returned by NetworkTablesJNI.now().
048   */
049  public long getTime() {
050    return m_time;
051  }
052
053  /*
054   * Type Checkers
055   */
056
057  /**
058   * Determine if entry value contains a value or is unassigned.
059   *
060   * @return True if the entry value contains a value.
061   */
062  public boolean isValid() {
063    return m_type != NetworkTableType.kUnassigned;
064  }
065
066  /**
067   * Determine if entry value contains a boolean.
068   *
069   * @return True if the entry value is of boolean type.
070   */
071  public boolean isBoolean() {
072    return m_type == NetworkTableType.kBoolean;
073  }
074
075  /**
076   * Determine if entry value contains a double.
077   *
078   * @return True if the entry value is of double type.
079   */
080  public boolean isDouble() {
081    return m_type == NetworkTableType.kDouble;
082  }
083
084  /**
085   * Determine if entry value contains a string.
086   *
087   * @return True if the entry value is of string type.
088   */
089  public boolean isString() {
090    return m_type == NetworkTableType.kString;
091  }
092
093  /**
094   * Determine if entry value contains a raw.
095   *
096   * @return True if the entry value is of raw type.
097   */
098  public boolean isRaw() {
099    return m_type == NetworkTableType.kRaw;
100  }
101
102  /**
103   * Determine if entry value contains a rpc definition.
104   *
105   * @return True if the entry value is of rpc definition type.
106   */
107  public boolean isRpc() {
108    return m_type == NetworkTableType.kRpc;
109  }
110
111  /**
112   * Determine if entry value contains a boolean array.
113   *
114   * @return True if the entry value is of boolean array type.
115   */
116  public boolean isBooleanArray() {
117    return m_type == NetworkTableType.kBooleanArray;
118  }
119
120  /**
121   * Determine if entry value contains a double array.
122   *
123   * @return True if the entry value is of double array type.
124   */
125  public boolean isDoubleArray() {
126    return m_type == NetworkTableType.kDoubleArray;
127  }
128
129  /**
130   * Determine if entry value contains a string array.
131   *
132   * @return True if the entry value is of string array type.
133   */
134  public boolean isStringArray() {
135    return m_type == NetworkTableType.kStringArray;
136  }
137
138  /*
139   * Type-Safe Getters
140   */
141
142  /**
143   * Get the entry's boolean value.
144   *
145   * @return The boolean value.
146   * @throws ClassCastException if the entry value is not of boolean type.
147   */
148  public boolean getBoolean() {
149    if (m_type != NetworkTableType.kBoolean) {
150      throw new ClassCastException("cannot convert " + m_type + " to boolean");
151    }
152    return (Boolean) m_value;
153  }
154
155  /**
156   * Get the entry's double value.
157   *
158   * @return The double value.
159   * @throws ClassCastException if the entry value is not of double type.
160   */
161  public double getDouble() {
162    if (m_type != NetworkTableType.kDouble) {
163      throw new ClassCastException("cannot convert " + m_type + " to double");
164    }
165    return ((Number) m_value).doubleValue();
166  }
167
168  /**
169   * Get the entry's string value.
170   *
171   * @return The string value.
172   * @throws ClassCastException if the entry value is not of string type.
173   */
174  public String getString() {
175    if (m_type != NetworkTableType.kString) {
176      throw new ClassCastException("cannot convert " + m_type + " to string");
177    }
178    return (String) m_value;
179  }
180
181  /**
182   * Get the entry's raw value.
183   *
184   * @return The raw value.
185   * @throws ClassCastException if the entry value is not of raw type.
186   */
187  public byte[] getRaw() {

192  }

226  public double[] getDoubleArray() {

460  @Override
461  public boolean equals(Object other) {
462    if (other == this) {
463      return true;
464    }
465    if (!(other instanceof NetworkTableValue)) {
466      return false;
467    }
468    NetworkTableValue ntOther = (NetworkTableValue) other;
469    return m_type == ntOther.m_type && m_value.equals(ntOther.m_value);
470  }
471
472  @Override
473  public int hashCode() {
474    return Objects.hash(m_type, m_value);
475  }
476
477  // arraycopy() doesn't know how to unwrap boxed values; this is a false positive in PMD
478  // (see https://sourceforge.net/p/pmd/bugs/804/)
479  @SuppressWarnings("PMD.AvoidArrayLoops")
480  static boolean[] toNative(Boolean[] arr) {
481    boolean[] out = new boolean[arr.length];
482    for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
483      out[i] = arr[i];
484    }
485    return out;
486  }
487
488  @SuppressWarnings("PMD.AvoidArrayLoops")
489  static double[] toNative(Number[] arr) {
490    double[] out = new double[arr.length];
491    for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
492      out[i] = arr[i].doubleValue();
493    }
494    return out;
495  }
496
497  @SuppressWarnings("PMD.AvoidArrayLoops")
498  static Boolean[] fromNative(boolean[] arr) {
499    Boolean[] out = new Boolean[arr.length];
500    for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
501      out[i] = arr[i];
502    }
503    return out;
504  }
505
506  @SuppressWarnings("PMD.AvoidArrayLoops")
507  static Double[] fromNative(double[] arr) {
508    Double[] out = new Double[arr.length];
509    for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
510      out[i] = arr[i];
511    }
512    return out;
513  }
514
515  private NetworkTableType m_type;
516  private Object m_value;
517  private long m_time;
